 Security & Operational notes- Run in isolated network. Block outgoing traffic other than defined log forwarding endpoints.- Rotate and protect collected logs (sensitive PII may appear).- Limit access to honeypot admin interfaces; use jump boxes and MFA for management.- Keep honeypot images up-to-date and monitor resource usage.
 Example docker-compose.yml (snippet)
 version: '3.8'
 services:
  cowrie:
    image: cowrie/cowrie:latest
    volumes:
      - ./data/cowrie:/cowrie
    ports:
      - "${COWRIE_SSH_PORT:-2222}:2222"
  glastopf:
    image: darkoperator/glastopf:latest
    volumes:
      - ./data/glastopf:/glastopf/log
    ports:
      - "${GLASTOPF_HTTP_PORT:-8080}:80"
  filebeat:
    image: docker.elastic.co/beats/filebeat:8.0.0
 Sample Ansible playbook (snippet)- name: Provision honeypot host and deploy docker-compose
  hosts: honeypot_hosts
  become: yes
  tasks:
    - name: Ensure apt cache updated
      apt:
        update_cache: yes
    - name: Install Docker
      apt:
        name: docker-ce
        state: present
